 Oligonucleotide probes can be stripped off the membrane very easily which is useful. Probes should not be designed with a C at the 5\u2032 end as this inhibits labeling. Clean the oligonucleotide probe using a QIAquick Nucleotide Removal Kit before labeling.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"F41AE0599B564ED7AEA2E8DACF219A46","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">RNA or LNA oligos can also be employed to improve specificity but the hybridization conditions will need to be optimised.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":10200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1059270,"guid":"2F8E3B6F9B6A4085B09A34FFE0FAE40F","previous_id":1059269,"previous_guid":"96662F9BD3674083B0E511A447A79EB9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8DD2442A75324E51A64B30112A86DED0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Hybridization of DNA Oligonucleotide Probes"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DA2D58704B1F4070B46A0C2EE99DAA86","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Ensure that the hybridization bottles and internal seals are in good condition to avoid radioactive buffer leaking during hybridization.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":10200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1059271,"guid":"83C4B383418340F6AFDAE39886EB3989","previous_id":1059270,"previous_guid":"2F8E3B6F9B6A4085B09A34FFE0FAE40F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D70336F5346B4F2A84DA095081FB8544","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Hybridization of DNA Oligonucleotide Probes"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"CA433AEDAEFD47D69581DF5365B3A4FC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prewarm a bottle of ULTRAHyb Oligo to <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> until the SDS fully dissolves (<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\u2013<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">).<\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"02FE4B000CF611EB902293CDC15792DA","order_id":2,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":68,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"5C06A750172911EB8664FFA911CE0A44","order_id":3,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":900,"title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"075214C00CF611EB902293CDC15792DA","order_id":4,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1200,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":10200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":2100},{"id":1059272,"guid":"F8377D0B5B7649788571CC3627392368","previous_id":1059271,"previous_guid":"83C4B383418340F6AFDAE39886EB3989","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5AD02353174B474CA0816E0CF7C4282D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Hybridization of DNA Oligonucleotide Probes"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AF6C838195EA4DD6AF99128478C4CDE3","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wet the membrane with 0.1\u00d7 SSC 0.1% SDS. Roll it up with the RNA facing inward, drop it into the hybridization bottle and slowly turn the bottle to unroll the membrane against the side of the bottle.<\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D7370E58B2C54C0C890B093B68DFB4D2","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">A Stripette can be used to help with this. Push out any obvious air bubbles. Put bottles in the oven so that the visible edge of the membrane is moving with the direction of rotation; if the membrane rolls up into a thin cigar during hybridization or washing then it was the wrong way round. When using a hybridization oven with rotisserie, always be sure to balance the bottles, including the volume of liquid inside. Two membranes can be hybridized in the same bottle, one facing the glass and the other facing the inside of the bottle.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":"","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":"","note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":10200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1059273,"guid":"DCD4F70F66374EF9903C48137563D81F","previous_id":1059272,"previous_guid":"F8377D0B5B7649788571CC3627392368","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"63FE72F953B1482E9E686E169EB711C6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Hybridization of DNA Oligonucleotide Probes"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6C90DC77314D4F728746646C6FEC4DBA","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"tit